A '''haversack''', or havresack (through the French frog [[German language|Ger.]] Habersack, an oat-sack, a nose-bag, Hafer or Haver, [[oat]]s) the bag in which horsemen carried the oats for their horses In [[Scotland]] and the north of [[England]] hazer, meaning oats, is still used, as haver-meal or haver-bread. Haversack is now used for the strong bag made of [[linen]] or [[canvas]], in which [[soldier]]s, sportsmen or travellers, carry their personal belongings, or more usually the provisions for the day.

